{
  "texts": [
    "For example, changing \"T1\" and \"Al 2 CuLi\" into \"T1-Al 2 CuLi\" or \"Al 3 Sc x Zr 1-x \" and \"Al 3 Sc 1-x Zr x \" into \"Al 3 (Sc,Zr).",
    "\"The fourth step was disambiguation, which, for our database, mostly focused on the \" \" phase.",
    "In aluminum literature, \" \" can refer to multiple distinct phases: Mg 2 Si, Al 5 FeSi, or Al 3 Mg 2.",
    "We disambiguated phase entities by looking at chemical names appearing in the same sentence or the paragraph containing the sentence.",
    "For example, if exactly one the chemical formulae ( Mg 2 Si, Al 5 FeSi, or Al 3 Mg 2) appeared in the sentence or the paragraph then this was used to determine the specific phase."
  ]
}